# Fixture: fm12-subquery-projection-list
# Finding: Subquery projection — outer query references variable not
#          projected by the inner SELECT
# Spec: SPARQL 1.1 §12.3.2 (subquery scoping)
#
# Hypothesis: A subquery's SELECT clause determines which variables are
# "in scope" for the outer query. Variables bound inside the subquery but
# NOT in its SELECT list are NOT visible to the outer query. The outer
# query referencing such a variable (?internal) produces an unbound
# variable, which may silently evaluate to an empty result or be an error.
#
# Divergence: An implementation that leaks inner-subquery bindings through
# the subquery's SELECT boundary will bind ?internal in the outer query;
# correct behaviour is that ?internal is unbound or absent. This is the
# projection-list edge case — what is *not* projected is as important as
# what is.
# Grammar-level behaviour: parses successfully; divergence at evaluation.

SELECT ?s ?o ?internal WHERE {
  ?s <http://example/p> ?o .
  {
    SELECT ?s WHERE {
      ?s <http://example/p> ?o .
      BIND(42 AS ?internal)
    }
  }
}
